<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <d4p_MathML><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>exp</m:mi><m:mo>⁡</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></d4p_MathML>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
, with alternating signs,
</p><d4p_eqn_block>
  <d4p_MathML><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>sin</m:mi><m:mo>⁡</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>!</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>!</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mo>⋯</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></d4p_MathML>
</d4p_eqn_block><p>
We can set up a spreadsheet to compute it in many ways, and here is one.
</p><p>
